{
  "texts": [
    "In this method, instead of aggregating the item scores from all four runs as in the primary analysis, component scores were calculated by aggregating the item scores from runs 1 and 2, as well as from runs 3 and 4.",
    "The three component scores exhibited inter-correlations of r = 0.56, 0.81, and 0.70.",
    "The correlations in Table 3 indicate the extent to which the three component scores predicted altmetrics and citation scores.",
    "The Quality and Reliability component displayed Note Loadings exceeding 0.40 or falling below -0.40 are depicted in boldface (see Peterson, 2000, who identified that a common loading cutoff value is 0.40) weak positive correlations with the number of citations (ρ = 0.05 to 0.10 for the three citation measures).",
    "Furthermore, weak correlations were observed between Quality and Reliability and the altmetrics."
  ]
}